  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section firstReview">
      

<div id="review_2699907524" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2699907524" />
    <a title="Sherri Moorer" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/7550002-sherri-moorer"><img alt="Sherri Moorer" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1558812549p2/7550002.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2699907524?book_show_action=true">Feb 13, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sherri Moorer" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sherri Moorer" href="/user/show/7550002-sherri-moorer">Sherri Moorer</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2699907524" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17620826393350795465">Jack Dylan is riding the wake of a triumph over white supremacists in his small town of Dearborn, Michigan, when he discovers that another plot has hatched. The leader of another syndicate has vowed revenge for the arrest of a friend through a sarin attack on Dearborn. Jack and the rest of the Dearborn force are working diligently to thwart the attack when the FBI steps in and ururps the investigation. Frustrated, Jack decides to strike off on his own after the leader when he gets a tip that the</span>
  <span id="freeText17620826393350795465" style="display:none">Jack Dylan is riding the wake of a triumph over white supremacists in his small town of Dearborn, Michigan, when he discovers that another plot has hatched. The leader of another syndicate has vowed revenge for the arrest of a friend through a sarin attack on Dearborn. Jack and the rest of the Dearborn force are working diligently to thwart the attack when the FBI steps in and ururps the investigation. Frustrated, Jack decides to strike off on his own after the leader when he gets a tip that the man behind the sarin plot is on a fishing boat in Manistee. The plot nearly works, until Jack makes a careless mistake that blows his cover, and winds diving in a lake to save himself from a grenade attack. The Manistee police are furious with Jack for launching an undercover operation in their jurisdiction without permission, and arrest him on charges of stalking and suspected murder. Arrested and alone, Jack calls his friend, defense attorney Zachary Blake, to defend him against the charges, clear his name, and unravel the rest of the story that happened on that fishing boat. Betrayal in Blue, by Mark M. Bello, is an entertaining journey through the criminal justice process, from the planned crime to the aftermath of the trial. <br /><br />I like Betrayal in Blue because it shows readers the entire process, from crime to court, and beyond. I learned a great deal about investigations and collecting evidence, and the story is fascinating.Jack Dylan and Zachary Blake may seem stereotypical cops and lawyers on the surface, but this book exposes a deeper character in both of them that shows how their integrity makes them successful. The story is entertaining, and has plenty of twists to keep you wondering how it will end, and even gifts you with a glimpse beyond the end as the story continues past the perceived "ending" of the story. It just goes to show that it's never truly over! I anticipate that Jack and Zachary both have many shared adventures to come. Mark M. Bello has created a compelling world with a rich and diverse cast of characters that make this tale intriguing - and no doubt, will share many more stories to come!</span>
  <a data-text-id="17620826393350795465" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


