  <span id="freeText2197321120484311404" style="display:none">This third book in the Zachary Blake Legal Thriller Series by Mark M Bello was definitely a fast-paced thrill ride combining action involving an unofficial police battle with a White Supremacist along with a tense legal battle in court defending that police officer. Zack utilizes his usual group of experts to hopefully find that one key piece of evidence that will or will not exonerate his client. The characters in this book are fairly well described and fleshed out. The story moves along a nice even pace from opening salvo to the final words. I am looking forward to reading book 4 in this series which I already have in my TBR file. This is a voluntary review of this book from Fast and Free Reviews.</span>
