<span id="freeTextContainer15781914596838658208">Betrayal in Blue is Mark M. Bello’s third novel in A Zachary Blake Legal Thriller, and I think it is the best so far. Police Captain Jack Dylan is in hot pursuit of a white supremacist, Bart Breitner, who is seeking revenge for capturing his leader. After the FBI messed up the only lead they had, Jack goes after him undercover, as a civilian. When Jack gets himself in trouble, he calls Zack Blake. Can Zack pull the evidence together in time to clear Jack’s name?<br/> <br/>I love Mark M. Bello’s Zachary Bl</span>
  <span id="freeText15781914596838658208" style="display:none">Betrayal in Blue is Mark M. Bello’s third novel in A Zachary Blake Legal Thriller, and I think it is the best so far. Police Captain Jack Dylan is in hot pursuit of a white supremacist, Bart Breitner, who is seeking revenge for capturing his leader. After the FBI messed up the only lead they had, Jack goes after him undercover, as a civilian. When Jack gets himself in trouble, he calls Zack Blake. Can Zack pull the evidence together in time to clear Jack’s name?<br /> <br />I love Mark M. Bello’s Zachary Blake legal thrillers. As with each book, Betrayal in Blue can be read by itself, but you get the picture of the characters if you read them in order. Zachary Blake is a dedicated and thorough attorney, who will employ all his resources to clear his clients. The author implements a complex web of mystery and drama that will keep the reader glued to the pages. Overall, I loved reading this novel and look forward to Betrayal in Black.</span>
