<div id="review_3148331333" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3148331333" />
    <a title="the-librarian" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/103684610-the-librarian"><img alt="the-librarian" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1570282445p2/103684610.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3148331333?book_show_action=true">Jan 18, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="the-librarian" class="user" itemprop="url" name="the-librarian" href="/user/show/103684610-the-librarian">the-librarian</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/49079091-betrayal-in-blue">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3148331333" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2078056629522776886">Super lawyer Zachary Blake is back in action in the third installment of the Zachary Blake Legal Thriller series of novels. If you have not read the first two books, you should definitely go out and do so now. Not because it is required to understand this book, but it is a lot of fun to watch the character growth and development from the beginning. If you haven’t read either of them, you can certainly still pick this one up and not be lost though.<br/><br/>This time Zack finds himself fighting against pol</span>
  <span id="freeText2078056629522776886" style="display:none">Super lawyer Zachary Blake is back in action in the third installment of the Zachary Blake Legal Thriller series of novels. If you have not read the first two books, you should definitely go out and do so now. Not because it is required to understand this book, but it is a lot of fun to watch the character growth and development from the beginning. If you haven’t read either of them, you can certainly still pick this one up and not be lost though.<br /><br />This time Zack finds himself fighting against police. FBI resources, and white supremacists (again) to protect his old enemy, Captain Jack Dylan, from false terrorism charges. This time the case takes place in a small northern Michigan fishing town. As with the rest of the series, the book is really well written and is exciting with compelling characters and plenty of plot twists to hold your interest. All of the plot lines hold together and makes for an interesting story overall.<br /><br />Overall, this is another strong entry by author Mark M. Bello. With plenty of interesting investigations, chasing, evidence discovery, and trial intrigue to keep anyones interest for the whole book. If you enjoy a good legal/crime thriller, it would be difficult to go wrong in picking this one up. While you’re at it, you may as well pick up the other two books in the series as well because if you like this one you will definitely want to read the rest of the series.</span>
  <a data-text-id="2078056629522776886" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


