  <span id="freeText7301904817750154129" style="display:none">This is another great crime thriller from Bello. The plot of this book follows a similar theme as the last regarding a storm brewing in the U.S. around immigration and in particular muslims. The story is very well thought out and feels as realistic as all the other books. The plot is riveting and the the switching between characters (in all of the books I've read so far) is a great way to see all points of view regardless of whether you agree with them or not, and that's even more important when the events feel so realistic. I'm really enjoying the series and can't wait to get to the next one. </span>
