<div id="review_2715993978" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2715993978" />
    <a title="Mrs. Varela " class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2430315-mrs-varela"><img alt="Mrs. Varela " src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1612735814p2/2430315.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2715993978?book_show_action=true">Feb 22, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Mrs. Varela " class="user" itemprop="url" name="Mrs. Varela " href="/user/show/2430315-mrs-varela">Mrs. Varela </a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2715993978" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12608901192774725463">Betrayal in Blue is a very well written legal thriller set in the cities of Dearborn and Manistee, Michigan. The city of Dearborn has recently recovered from the bombing of a Muslim mosque and the ensuing trial of  Arya Khan, a Muslim woman accused of setting the bomb. Attorney Zachary Blake represents Arya and she is found innocent. The true culprits were a group of white supremacists. When their leader is arrested and found guilty of the crime, his followers plan to seek revenge with yet anoth</span>
  <span id="freeText12608901192774725463" style="display:none">Betrayal in Blue is a very well written legal thriller set in the cities of Dearborn and Manistee, Michigan. The city of Dearborn has recently recovered from the bombing of a Muslim mosque and the ensuing trial of  Arya Khan, a Muslim woman accused of setting the bomb. Attorney Zachary Blake represents Arya and she is found innocent. The true culprits were a group of white supremacists. When their leader is arrested and found guilty of the crime, his followers plan to seek revenge with yet another terrorist act in Dearborn. When Captain Jack Dylan, head of the city’s Terrorism Task Force is notified about the possibility that the city is again being targeted, he and his team are determined to make sure any act of terrorism doesn’t happen, but the FBI steps in to derail their plans. One very dangerous man escapes under the FBI’s watch and an angry Jack Dylan decides to go after him on his own.<br /><br /><br />In his haste to find and arrest the terrorist, Captain Dylan heads to Manistee and goes undercover without notice to any of the authorities in Dearborn, Manistee or to the FBI. When his plans begin to go terribly wrong he finds himself arrested by the local authorities for his deceptive actions.<br /><br /><br />In deep trouble and in need of representation, attorney Zachary Blake shows up on the scene to defend Jack. It’s a royal battle for Zachary when all evidence points to his client’s guilt. With Zachary being one of the best attorneys in MIchigan and a team of experts on hand he goes all out to win and find a smoking gun that could help find Jack innocent.<br /><br /><br />This a mind-blowing story with a shocking and intense ending that will have readers sitting on the edge of their seats.</span>
  <a data-text-id="12608901192774725463" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


