<span id="freeTextContainer4762160741159876684">This is the 4th book of the series that I have read. Even though I was aware of the final conclusion, I was still interested to read this and found out all of the details.<br/><br/>This story has the Dearborn Police task force discovering a plot against them as well as a Muslim mosque in their town because of their success in bring another White Supremacist group to justice earlier and this new group wanted revenge. The information eventually gets provided to the FBI who immediately takes control of the c</span>
  <span id="freeText4762160741159876684" style="display:none">This is the 4th book of the series that I have read. Even though I was aware of the final conclusion, I was still interested to read this and found out all of the details.<br /><br />This story has the Dearborn Police task force discovering a plot against them as well as a Muslim mosque in their town because of their success in bring another White Supremacist group to justice earlier and this new group wanted revenge. The information eventually gets provided to the FBI who immediately takes control of the case. While an operation was set up by the FBI to thwart the White Supremacist group from obtaining chemical weapons. They were successful except for the fact that the leader of this group escaped.<br /><br />Jack Daly the Captain on the Task Force received information that he used to go undercover to capture this individual. Unfortunately, all did not go like planned and Jack was charged with murder of the group leader. Zach was hired to defend Jack and with the assistance of Micah Love's team and 3 of the task force members, they were able to obtain evidence which could aide Zach with Jack's defense.<br /><br />The description of how the evidence was gathered and the actual trail really plays into the meat of the book. The ending is well worth it and has a surprise in it. To find out how the whole story ends, then you must read this book. You won't be disappointed.</span>
  <a data-text-id="4762160741159876684" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
