<div id="review_2780889949" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2780889949" />
    <a title="Kathleen Kelly" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2714432-kathleen-kelly"><img alt="Kathleen Kelly" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1308841827p2/2714432.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2780889949?book_show_action=true">Apr 30, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kathleen Kelly" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kathleen Kelly" href="/user/show/2714432-kathleen-kelly">Kathleen Kelly</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2780889949" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9272207592301022701">Betrayal in Blue by Mark M. Bello is a story of one man&apos;s determination to find the leader of the white supremacists, Bart Breitner. The story starts out with a group of men, the elite unit of the Dearborn Michigan police officers. They received notoriety for arresting a group of white supremacists and in the process exonerating Arya Khan, a Muslim woman who had been accused of killing a mosque bomber, who later was held, hostage. <br/><br/><br/>As this is going on, they find out that there is a plot to releas</span>
  <span id="freeText9272207592301022701" style="display:none">Betrayal in Blue by Mark M. Bello is a story of one man's determination to find the leader of the white supremacists, Bart Breitner. The story starts out with a group of men, the elite unit of the Dearborn Michigan police officers. They received notoriety for arresting a group of white supremacists and in the process exonerating Arya Khan, a Muslim woman who had been accused of killing a mosque bomber, who later was held, hostage. <br /><br /><br />As this is going on, they find out that there is a plot to release a gas called Sarin. This is a gas that was developed by the Germans in 1938, it was used in an attack in Japan, and more recently used in Syria. Now the white supremacists want to use the gas in Washington. The police now need to find out all they can about sarin and the plot. Fortunately, the plot is destroyed and the sarin collected. One of the detectives, Captain Jack Dylan is not happy with all of this, he wants to find Bart Breitner at all costs. Not only that, the Muslim community is endangered and Jack does what he can to notify the community by attending evening worship at Imam Ghafari's Mosque of America to warn the worshipers of their risk from the white supremacists.<br /><br /><br />Jack decides to go after Bart undercover and prepares to go on a fishing trip but wants to go and join Bart's group of supremacists, which he does. Jack does have a group of other police officers as back up for whatever assistance he may need. Unfortunately for Jack, on a meeting on Bart's boat, he accidentally calls Bart Bert which is now a problem for Jack. Bart threatens to shoot Jack. Jack is credulous that Bart would shoot him over a mispronouncing of his name. Now a backup officer listening in, Shaheed, calls 911 for further assistance. Breitner has a grenade and uses it. Jack jumps overboard to protect himself. The local police of Manistee hold Jack and charge him with murder. They sift around for clues and find blood and body parts in the water which is enough for them to arrest him. They don't like that Jack did an undercover investigation on their turf so they don't like Jack and make it as hard for Jack as they can. Jack gets his friend Zack who is a high profile lawyer. Next is a trial and to give away more of the story I will stop here.<br /><br />What I did not like about the book, I couldn't really find anything I did not like about the book, except the bad guys, nothing that the author did or did not do. It was interesting to learn more about sarin and white supremacists. I did not read the previous two books, I would have liked to learn more about the relationship between Jack and his lawyer Zach Blake, so I may just go and read the first two books in the series, as it appears that the author Mark M. Bello knows his stuff when it comes to police procedurals. This book will appeal to the reader who loves the mystery/murder/police procedurals genres there is some violence but not too descriptive. If you don't like this kind of book then I would not recommend it. <br /><br />What I liked about Betrayal in Blue by Mark M. Bello? I am an avid reader of mystery/procedural stories and I really liked this book. It is written professionally, no grammar issues that I could find. The story flowed from beginning to end. The main character, Jack, is a character that you can feel and know that he is a man with issues but has a determination to do the right thing. I was able to read the book without getting bored, a page-turner. This is an intense courtroom drama and I give it 4 out of 4 stars.</span>
  <a data-text-id="9272207592301022701" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


