<div id="review_2700787853" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2700787853" />
    <a title="Bonnie" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/44364621-bonnie"><img alt="Bonnie" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2700787853?book_show_action=true">Feb 03, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Bonnie" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Bonnie" href="/user/show/44364621-bonnie">Bonnie</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2700787853" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8672356067321741124">Three Stars for Betrayal in Blue by Mark M. Bello. This is the third book in this series, but the first one I have read. References were made to the subject of the first book, but if you didn’t read it, it doesn’t impact the gist of the third. If references were made from the second book, I did not notice them.<br/><br/>Mr. Bello tells a great story. It was engaging throughout, and the entire time reading it, I thought it would make a good movie or TV show. The main character, Jack Dylan, is an honorable </span>
  <span id="freeText8672356067321741124" style="display:none">Three Stars for Betrayal in Blue by Mark M. Bello. This is the third book in this series, but the first one I have read. References were made to the subject of the first book, but if you didn’t read it, it doesn’t impact the gist of the third. If references were made from the second book, I did not notice them.<br /><br />Mr. Bello tells a great story. It was engaging throughout, and the entire time reading it, I thought it would make a good movie or TV show. The main character, Jack Dylan, is an honorable police officer, and it’s clear he has a cohesive team. <br /><br />Dylan tells his boss he needs some R and R, then goes out of town to chase after a terrorist by himself. Only a few select people know what he’s up to. This is when things backfire on him and is is arrested for murder. The local police force and FBI think he’s guilty rather than backing him up, despite the lack of evidence and lack of a dead body.<br /><br />The chapters involving the trial were the best. It was like being there. I loved Judge Shipley’s personality and reasonableness. Zack, Jack’s defense attorney, is likeable as well. You have to feel for the prosecutor somewhat, and Chief Alexander? He’s the guy you love to hate.<br /><br />The story itself is a good 3 stars and has potential for 4 stars, except I found the dialogue did not flow as well as it could have. In many places it seemed too formal and unnatural somehow, however, the courtroom dialogue was stellar. <br /><br />I read this book on kindle, and perhaps that is the reason why there are formatting issues. There were paragraphs highlighted, but there was nothing special in the highlighted areas to suggest the highlighting was intentional. There were several paragraphs needing indentation, a handful of punctuation mishaps, and sentences that read awkwardly or the editing was not proofread. The number of semicolons used throughout the book was a bit distracting. <br /><br />I would definitely read more from this author, but hope the next book I read from him is edited better.</span>
  <a data-text-id="8672356067321741124" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

