<span id="freeTextContainer14859316272946396009"><strong>Betrayal in Blue</strong><br/><br/>Captain Jack Dylan is head of the Terrorist task force in Dearborn Michigan, he and his team get wind of a terrorist plot to set of a deadly gas at the Dearborn police station and in the Muslim community by a white supremacy group. In their efforts to locate and stop the plan, the FBI step in and take the case. They botch the job and the ring leader gets away. Jack learns of his whereabouts and sets off unofficially to try and find the guy. While undercover in another town with n</span>
  <span id="freeText14859316272946396009" style="display:none"><strong>Betrayal in Blue</strong><br /><br />Captain Jack Dylan is head of the Terrorist task force in Dearborn Michigan, he and his team get wind of a terrorist plot to set of a deadly gas at the Dearborn police station and in the Muslim community by a white supremacy group. In their efforts to locate and stop the plan, the FBI step in and take the case. They botch the job and the ring leader gets away. Jack learns of his whereabouts and sets off unofficially to try and find the guy. While undercover in another town with no jurisdiction he finds Bart and befriends him, while on this guys boat, Bart figures out who Jack is and tries to kill him by setting off a grenade. Jack jumps in the water to safety only to be arrested by the local police whom believe Jack killed Bart. A long trial takes place and the locals and the FBI all believe Jack is guilty, so when his big city lawyer comes in and shreds their case they are none to happy. Jack is released and free to go. After Jack is back home and at the office, a visitor sneaks in and wearing a suicide vest takes a Jack hostage and insists that his lawyer come to the police station. Turns out Bart wasn’t blown up by the grenade and now wants revenge. Jack and his lawyer have to do a lot of fancy talking and bluffing until the swat team can take out Bart. Jack and his lawyer are safe and life can get back to normal.</span>
  <a data-text-id="14859316272946396009" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
