<div id="review_2978210058" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2978210058" />
    <a title="Mehrnaz Siavoshi" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/32030371-mehrnaz-siavoshi"><img alt="Mehrnaz Siavoshi" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1433391115p2/32030371.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2978210058?book_show_action=true">Sep 26, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Mehrnaz Siavoshi" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Mehrnaz Siavoshi" href="/user/show/32030371-mehrnaz-siavoshi">Mehrnaz Siavoshi</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/32030371-mehrnaz-siavoshi?shelf=for-review">for-review</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/32030371-mehrnaz-siavoshi?shelf=thriller">thriller</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2978210058" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13679222368884002598"><a href='https://forums.onlinebookclub.org/viewtopic.php?f=22&amp;t=120477' rel='nofollow noopener'>Full review and discussion here. </a><br/><br/><i>I received a free copy of this book in exchange for an honest review.</i><br/><br/>This was a super fast-paced book that I was able to get through surprisingly quickly. It tells the story of Dearborn Police Captain Jack Dylan’s struggles to capture white supremacist and terrorist Barton Breitner. The story as a whole was exciting, but it was highly predictable and followed every trope I could think of in the legal thriller genre. Overall, I give it <b>
  <u>3.25 stars</u>
</b>. <br/><br/>The highligh</span>
  <span id="freeText13679222368884002598" style="display:none"><a href="https://forums.onlinebookclub.org/viewtopic.php?f=22&amp;t=120477" rel="nofollow noopener">Full review and discussion here. </a><br /><br /><i>I received a free copy of this book in exchange for an honest review.</i><br /><br />This was a super fast-paced book that I was able to get through surprisingly quickly. It tells the story of Dearborn Police Captain Jack Dylan’s struggles to capture white supremacist and terrorist Barton Breitner. The story as a whole was exciting, but it was highly predictable and followed every trope I could think of in the legal thriller genre. Overall, I give it <b>
  <u>3.25 stars</u>
</b>. <br /><br />The highlights of this book are its fast pace. There was no point in reading it where I was bored, even though it does follow a predictable structure. While the structure itself was predictable and I knew a plot twist was coming, the specific plot twists were interesting and thought out. <br /><br />The one biggest thing that took me out of the book was the research-based parts. There was a section in particular where one character was explaining what sarin gas was to another and I felt like that section could have come straight out of a Wikipedia article.<br /><br />Ultimately, I don't think this book is bad. I think it deserves a lot of the same criticisms that crime dramas like Law and Order: SVU get, but that does not make it a poor book. In fact, I would recommend this book wholeheartedly to anyone who loves those types of shows. <br /><br />It didn't do anything exciting or change the genre for me. In fact, I would not say this book is memorable. All this together is why I rated it at 3.25 stars.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13679222368884002598" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


